name: Romeo & Juliet
description: Romeo & Juliet is one of the original six quests released with the launch of RuneScape. The quest roughly follows the storyline of the tragedy of the same name by William Shakespeare.
completionRequirements: About the Old School RuneScape Wiki

name: Demon Slayer
description: Demon Slayer is one of six quests released with the launch of RuneScape. In it, players are tasked with protecting Varrock from a powerful demon.
completionRequirements: Recipe for Disaster/Freeing the Lumbridge Guide
About the Old School RuneScape Wiki

name: Shield of Arrav
description: Shield of Arrav is a quest where the shield of the famous Arrav of Avarrocka has been stolen by organised crime syndicates in Varrock.
completionRequirements: About the Old School RuneScape Wiki

name: Ernest the Chicken
description: Ernest the Chicken is a free-to-play quest where players must discover what happened to the missing Ernest, who went into Draynor Manor to ask for directions and never returned.
completionRequirements: About the Old School RuneScape Wiki

name: Vampyre Slayer
description: Vampyre Slayer is a free-to-play quest that takes place in Draynor Village. The player is asked to slay the terrifying vampyre count Draynor terrorising the village that lives in a large mansion just north of Draynor, with the help of an experienced vampyre slayer.
completionRequirements: About the Old School RuneScape Wiki

name: Imp Catcher
description: The Wizard Grayzag has summoned hundreds of little imps. They have stolen a lot of things belonging to the Wizard Mizgog including his magic beads.
completionRequirements: About the Old School RuneScape Wiki

name: Prince Ali Rescue
description: Prince Ali Rescue is a free-to-play quest, and one of the first released. It's notable for allowing entry through the Al Kharid/Lumbridge gate without the fee of 10 coins. It also introduces characters who are a part of the Kharidian quest series.
completionRequirements: About the Old School RuneScape Wiki

name: Doric's Quest
description: Doric's Quest is a quest involving Doric the dwarf, who is happy to let the player use his anvils but first requestsÂ an errand.
completionRequirements: About the Old School RuneScape Wiki

name: Black Knights' Fortress
description: The Black Knights are up to no good. You are hired by the white knights to spy on them and destroy their secret weapon.
completionRequirements: About the Old School RuneScape Wiki

name: Witch's Potion
description: Witch's Potion is a free-to-play quest where players help the witch Hetty in making a magical potion.
completionRequirements: About the Old School RuneScape Wiki

name: Goblin Diplomacy
description: There's a disturbance in the Goblin Village. Help the goblins solve their dispute so the world doesn't have to worry about rioting goblins. Aim: to help the goblins decide which colour they will wear.
completionRequirements: Recipe for Disaster/Freeing the Goblin generals
About the Old School RuneScape Wiki

name: Pirate's Treasure
description: Pirate's Treasure is a quest in which you help the pirate Redbeard Frank obtain some Karamjan rum in return for the location of the treasure of One-Eyed Hector, his old captain.
completionRequirements: About the Old School RuneScape Wiki

name: Dragon Slayer I
description: Dragon Slayer I is a quest that focuses on the player's journey to slay Elvarg, the dragon of Crandor. Often described as the hardest, yet most rewarding quest available to free-to-play players, those who successfully complete it gain the ability to equip the rune platebody and green d'hide body (as well as their many variations), in addition to the dragon platebody.
completionRequirements: 2.2 Duke Horacio and the anti-dragon shield
2.8 Tips for the fight & potential strategies
About the Old School RuneScape Wiki

name: Rune Mysteries
description: Rune Mysteries is a novice level Free-to-play quest, and a requirement for mining rune essence within the Rune Essence mine or using lamps and books on runecraft.
completionRequirements: About the Old School RuneScape Wiki

name: Misthalin Mystery
description: Mod West, Mod Ash
leadDevelopers:
Mod Jed, Mod TomH,
Mod West, Mod Ash
completionRequirements: About the Old School RuneScape Wiki

name: X Marks the Spot
description: X Marks the Spot is an introductory quest of the Great Kourend quest series focusing on Veos' treasure hunt in Lumbridge.
completionRequirements: About the Old School RuneScape Wiki

name: Below Ice Mountain
description: Below Ice Mountain is a free-to-play quest that revolves around aiding an 'archaeologist', Willow, who seeks to open an ancient set of doors leading into the western side of Ice Mountain. The player needs to assemble Willow's old team, which is capable of opening the doors and gaining entry to what lies beyond...
completionRequirements: Desert Treasure II - The Fallen Empire
About the Old School RuneScape Wiki

name: Sheep Shearer
description: Sheep Shearer is one of the six quests available when RuneScape first launched. In it, players help Fred the Farmer shear his sheep.
completionRequirements: About the Old School RuneScape Wiki

name: Cook's Assistant
description: Cook's Assistant is the first RuneScape quest ever released, and one of the six quests available during RuneScape's launch. In the quest, the player must help the Cook of Lumbridge Castle make a birthday cake for Duke Horacio.
completionRequirements: About the Old School RuneScape Wiki

name: The Corsair Curse
description: The Corsair Curse is the second new free-to-play quest released with Old School RuneScape. In the quest, players help a captain resolve the mystery of his cursed crew.
completionRequirements: Oggy Oggy Oggy! Oi Oi Oi!
Star Wars: Episode II â Attack of the Clones
About the Old School RuneScape Wiki

name: The Knight's Sword
description: Sir Vyvin's squire is in trouble. He has accidentally lost Sir Vyvin's ceremonial sword. Help him find a replacement without Sir Vyvin finding out.
completionRequirements: About the Old School RuneScape Wiki

name: The Restless Ghost
description: The Restless Ghost is one of the six quests released with the launch of RuneScape. In it, the player helps the priest of the Lumbridge church get rid of the ghost that haunts the Lumbridge graveyard.
completionRequirements: About the Old School RuneScape Wiki

name: Druidic Ritual
description: Druidic Ritual is a novice quest that serves as the introduction to the Herblore skill. It takes place entirely in the vicinity of Taverley and is a fairly short quest.
completionRequirements: About the Old School RuneScape Wiki

name: Lost City
description: Lost City is a quest about the fairy land Zanaris. A group of adventurers have set up camp in Lumbridge Swamp, claiming to be searching for the mystical lost city. You must find the truth of this claim, and gain entrance to the moon of Gielinor, Zanaris.
completionRequirements: About the Old School RuneScape Wiki

name: Witch's House
description: Witch's House is a quest involving a boy whose ball had been lost in the garden of an unpleasant local witch, Nora T. Hagg. The adventurer is asked to retrieve it, having to figure out how to proceed in Nora's house along the way.
completionRequirements: Recipe for Disaster/Freeing the Lumbridge Guide
About the Old School RuneScape Wiki

name: Merlin's Crystal
description: Merlin's Crystal is the first quest in the Camelot quest series, and involves the player rescuing the wizard Merlin from a crystal.
completionRequirements: About the Old School RuneScape Wiki

name: Heroes' Quest
description: The Heroes' Quest is a quest that gives access to the Heroes' Guild in Burthorpe, by completing the guildmaster's rigorous initiation test.
completionRequirements: 2.1 The greatest heroes of the land
2.2.1.2 Getting a Grip on the key
2.3.1 Ice Spy with my Little Eye
About the Old School RuneScape Wiki

name: Scorpion Catcher
description: Scorpion Catcher is a quest in which Thormac, a wizard in the Sorcerer's Tower, has lost three of his scorpions. He tasks you with finding them for him.
completionRequirements: About the Old School RuneScape Wiki

name: Family Crest
description: Family Crest is a quest in which the player must retrieve three family crest pieces from the Fitzharmon brothers and return the crest to their father.
completionRequirements: About the Old School RuneScape Wiki

name: Fishing Contest
description: Fishing Contest is a quest in which the player has to earn the friendship of two dwarven brothers by securing a fishing trophy for them. Afterwards, they allow the player to use the dwarven passage underneath the mountain.
completionRequirements: About the Old School RuneScape Wiki

name: Tribal Totem
description: Tribal Totem is a quest that involves the retrieval of an artefact sacred to the Rantuki tribe of Karamja, which has been taken from them by the nobleman Lord Handelmort.
completionRequirements: About the Old School RuneScape Wiki

name: Monk's Friend
description: Monk's Friend is a short novice quest in which the monks of the Ardougne Monastery ask you to do them a couple of favours, allowing them to throw a party without any setbacks.
completionRequirements: About the Old School RuneScape Wiki

name: Temple of Ikov
description: Temple of Ikov is a quest featuring Lucien, a Mahjarrat. The quest revolves around the infiltration of the Temple of Ikov in order to steal a powerful artefact known as the Staff of Armadyl.
completionRequirements: 2.4 Side with the Guardians of Armadyl
About the Old School RuneScape Wiki

name: Clock Tower
description: Clock Tower is a quest that takes place in the Ardougne Clock Tower. The tower's mechanism has stopped working, and you are asked to retrieve its missing parts from the dungeons.
completionRequirements: About the Old School RuneScape Wiki

name: Holy Grail
description: The Holy Grail quest is the second part of the Camelot quest series, where you must help King Arthur find the holy grail. The grail is found to be missing from its original location in Entrana, protected by the Fisher King in the Fisher Realm.
completionRequirements: About the Old School RuneScape Wiki

name: Tree Gnome Village
description: Tree Gnome Village is the first quest in the Gnome quest series and focuses on the war between General Khazard's army and the Tree Gnomes. During the quest, you need to aid the gnomes by retrieving stolen orbs.
completionRequirements: About the Old School RuneScape Wiki

name: Fight Arena
description: Fight Arena is an intermediate quest. The quest is started south of Ardougne by the titular Fight Arena by talking to Lady Servil.
completionRequirements: About the Old School RuneScape Wiki

name: Hazeel Cult
description: Hazeel Cult is a novice quest that was released on 15 August 2002. It was the second quest to feature a Mahjarrat, and introduces Hazeel, a Zamorakian Mahjarrat that has been put into a state of torpor, and his followers are attempting to revive him in time for the next Ritual of Rejuvenation.
completionRequirements: About the Old School RuneScape Wiki

name: Sheep Herder
description: Sheep Herder is a novice quest associated with the Elf quest series. It begins with the revelation that some sheep have been infected with plague. The target of the quest is to herd the sick sheep, kill them and dispose of their remains to prevent the plague from spreading to the town. Herding the sheep can prove challenging, since they are not very cooperative.
completionRequirements: 2.1 A threat to public health and safety
About the Old School RuneScape Wiki

name: Plague City
description: Plague City is the first quest of the Elf quest series. The quest investigates a plague that has affected West Ardougne.
completionRequirements: About the Old School RuneScape Wiki

name: Sea Slug
description: Sea Slug is the first quest in the Sea Slug series, and is the only piece of content to prominently feature the Fishing Platform.
completionRequirements: About the Old School RuneScape Wiki

name: Waterfall Quest
description: Waterfall Quest is an intermediate quest about a legendary treasure hidden somewhere in the Baxtorian Falls. The waterfall holds the history of the great elven King Baxtorian and his wife Glarial.
completionRequirements: About the Old School RuneScape Wiki

name: Jungle Potion
description: Jungle Potion is a short quest taking place on Karamja. It involves gathering a handful of different herbs for Trufitus Shakaya, in order for him to perform a ritual to communicate with the island's gods.
completionRequirements: About the Old School RuneScape Wiki

name: The Grand Tree
description: The Grand Tree is a gnome quest centred on protecting the Grand Tree from dying upon the gnome race.
completionRequirements: About the Old School RuneScape Wiki

name: Underground Pass
description: Underground Pass is the third quest in the Elf quest series, and explores an extensive and perilous dungeon to the west of Ardougne. You must venture through the pass at the request of King Lathas, in order to help him destroy his corrupted brother Tyras.
completionRequirements: 2.2 Getting in and across the bridge
2.6 The cages and the obstacle maze
2.10.1 Collecting the four elements of Iban to imbue the doll
About the Old School RuneScape Wiki

name: Observatory Quest
description: The Observatory Quest is a quest where you must help the professor of the observatory repair the structure and restore it to its former glory.
completionRequirements: About the Old School RuneScape Wiki

name: The Tourist Trap
description: The Tourist Trap is an intermediate quest set in the Kharidian Desert. The quest involves an undercover rescue operation into a slave camp to save an Al Kharidian woman's daughter.
completionRequirements: About the Old School RuneScape Wiki

name: Watchtower
description: Watchtower is a quest about the conflict between Yanille and the ogres of Gu'Tanoth. It involves the restoration of the city's Watchtower so that it may defend itself against an ogre attack.
completionRequirements: About the Old School RuneScape Wiki

name: Dwarf Cannon
description: Dwarf Cannon is a short quest about the conflict between the dwarven outpost at the Coal truck mining site and local goblins. The quest provides access to the Dwarf multicannon, a powerful Ranged weapon.
completionRequirements: About the Old School RuneScape Wiki

name: Murder Mystery
description: Murder Mystery is a quest that investigates the murder of Lord Sinclair. The culprit is random for each player, so some investigation must be done to determine the murderer. However, there are plenty of clues to be found around the Sinclair Mansion.
completionRequirements: About the Old School RuneScape Wiki

name: The Dig Site
description: The Dig Site is a quest where you must pass an archaeology exam for the Varrock Museum to be able to excavate the site where the city of Saranthium previously stood, but you discover something else...
completionRequirements: 2.6 The Temple of the Empty Lord
About the Old School RuneScape Wiki

name: Gertrude's Cat
description: Gertrude's Cat is a short quest in which you have to find Fluffs, a lost pet cat owned by Gertrude. Completion of the quest allows you to adopt a feline companion of your very own.
completionRequirements: About the Old School RuneScape Wiki

name: Legends' Quest
description: Legends' Quest is a quest in which the player is sent by Guildmaster Radimus Erkle to explore and map the Kharazi Jungle on the southern part of Karamja, establish relations with the natives and obtain a gift from them.
completionRequirements: Recipe for Disaster/Freeing Sir Amik Varze
Legends Guild Shop of Useful Items.
About the Old School RuneScape Wiki

name: Death Plateau
description: Death Plateau is a short quest wherein you are to help the Burthorpe Imperial Guard gain access to the Death Plateau in order to defeat the hostile trolls.
completionRequirements: About the Old School RuneScape Wiki

name: Eadgar's Ruse
description: Eadgar's Ruse is a quest in the Troll series. It revolves around a certain item that needs to be obtained for the druids to continue their efforts to reclaim their stone circle.
completionRequirements: About the Old School RuneScape Wiki

name: Big Chompy Bird Hunting
description: Big Chompy Bird Hunting is a quest in which you help Rantz the ogre catch a chompy bird so that he may feed his children.
completionRequirements: About the Old School RuneScape Wiki

name: Elemental Workshop I
description: Elemental Workshop I is a quest in which you find a mysterious book in Seers' Village, guiding along the rediscovery of the eponymous workshop and the lost magical elemental ore.
completionRequirements: About the Old School RuneScape Wiki

name: Nature Spirit
description: Nature Spirit is a quest that takes place deep in the Mort Myre Swamp. The nature spirit Filliman Tarlock needs help restoring the Nature Grotto, his home, to its previous glory.
completionRequirements: About the Old School RuneScape Wiki

name: Priest in Peril
description: Priest in Peril is the first quest to take place in Morytania, and is required to enter the region. At the command of King Roald, you must head to the temple of Paterdomus to aid the monk Drezel with recovering the temple.
completionRequirements: About the Old School RuneScape Wiki

name: Regicide
description: Regicide is the fourth quest in the Elf quest series, where King Lathas sends the player to Tirannwn to kill his brother, King Tyras, and end his tyranny.
completionRequirements: About the Old School RuneScape Wiki

name: Tai Bwo Wannai Trio
description: Tai Bwo Wannai Trio is a quest that follows where Jungle Potion left off. The chief of Tai Bwo Wannai requests your help in reuniting his sons, requiring you to seek each of the three out and help them in a specific task. One requires aid in defeating the Shaikahan, another seeks the knowledge to catch Karambwan, and the third seeks some unusual foodstuffs before he'll return to the village. Completing their individual tasks requires coordinating between the sons. Upon completing said tasks, the sons return to Tai Bwo Wannai.
completionRequirements: About the Old School RuneScape Wiki

name: Troll Stronghold
description: Troll Stronghold is a quest about gaining access to the Troll Stronghold beneath Mount Trollheim in order to rescue Godric, a soldier from Burthorpe. It is the second quest in the Troll Series.
completionRequirements: About the Old School RuneScape Wiki

name: Shades of Mort'ton
description: Shades of Mort'ton is a quest that takes place in Morytania. The town of Mort'ton is overrun with Shades, and a strange affliction has taken over the townspeople. The player uncovers an old cure for the affliction and must help the village.
completionRequirements: About the Old School RuneScape Wiki

name: The Fremennik Trials
description: The Fremennik Trials is a quest about becoming an honorary member of the Fremennik people of Rellekka. Since they are not very friendly to outerlanders, you will have to pass their trials for them to accept you as one of their own.
completionRequirements: About the Old School RuneScape Wiki

name: Horror from the Deep
description: Horror from the Deep is an intermediate quest revolving around the mysterious disappearance of Jossik, keeper of the Lighthouse near the Fremennik Province. As the title suggests, the investigations lead to the discovery of very dangerous creatures living beneath the lighthouse.
completionRequirements: About the Old School RuneScape Wiki

name: Throne of Miscellania
description: Throne of Miscellania is a quest about the Fremennik island Miscellania. The king, Vargas, has unfortunately become a yeti, thus making him require a regent to rule his kingdom while he is unable to.
completionRequirements: About the Old School RuneScape Wiki

name: Monkey Madness I
description: Monkey Madness I is the fourth quest in the gnome quest series, and one of the most well-known quests in RuneScape. The quest brings the player to Ape Atoll, an island inhabited by civilised but unfriendly and high-level monkeys, in order to help Narnode Shareen track down his missing 10th Squad military unit.
completionRequirements: 3.2.4 The Light at the End of the Tunnel
About the Old School RuneScape Wiki

name: Haunted Mine
description: Haunted Mine is a quest that explores the depths of a maze-like mine located south of Mort Myre swamp rumoured to contain powerful crystals infused with Saradomin's power. It is similar in terms of gameplay to Underground Pass, relying mainly on the player's own aptitude for exploration and aiming to instil an eerie atmosphere throughout.
completionRequirements: About the Old School RuneScape Wiki

name: Troll Romance
description: Troll Romance is a quest revolving around the troll Ug and his unrequited love for another troll, Aga.
completionRequirements: About the Old School RuneScape Wiki

name: In Search of the Myreque
description: In Search of the Myreque is a quest taking place in Morytania. The enigmatic stranger Vanstrom Klause asks you to deliver weapons to an organisation called the Myreque, but things do not turn out to be as they seem.
completionRequirements: About the Old School RuneScape Wiki

name: Creature of Fenkenstrain
description: Creature of Fenkenstrain is a quest where you become the assistant of Dr Fenkenstrain and slowly uncover the history of his castle: the Lordship of the North Coast.
completionRequirements: About the Old School RuneScape Wiki

name: Roving Elves
description: Roving Elves is a sequel to the Waterfall Quest and Regicide. It revolves around consecrating the tomb of King Baxtorian on behalf of his and Glarial's grandson Islwyn, who is roving the forests of Isafdar with Eluned.
completionRequirements: About the Old School RuneScape Wiki

name: Ghosts Ahoy
description: Ghosts Ahoy is a quest in which you help the villagers of Port Phasmatys pass on to the afterlife.
completionRequirements: 2.3 The old crone and nettle tea
About the Old School RuneScape Wiki

name: One Small Favour
description: One Small Favour is a humorous quest in which you are asked to complete a favour, although things turn out to be less simple than that.
completionRequirements: About the Old School RuneScape Wiki

name: Mountain Daughter
description: Mountain Daughter is a quest in the Fremennik quest series. In the quest, the player must assist the chieftain of a mountain camp in the mountains east of Rellekka in finding his daughter.
completionRequirements: About the Old School RuneScape Wiki

name: Between a Rock...
description: Between a Rock... is a quest about helping the old dwarf Dondakan, who is trying to access a legendary gold mine south of Keldagrim, but is unable to penetrate inside.
completionRequirements: Star Wars: Episode IV â A New Hope
About the Old School RuneScape Wiki

name: The Feud
description: In aiding the trader Ali Morrisane, you encounter a conflict between two gangs in the Desert city Pollnivneach.
completionRequirements: Ali Baba and the Forty Thieves
About the Old School RuneScape Wiki

name: The Golem
description: The Golem is a quest centred around the remains of the city of Uzer in the Kharidian Desert. Long ago, the city, which was defended by an army of clay golems, was destroyed at the hands of the demon Thammaron, leaving only ruins and a single clay golem remaining. You must utilise this golem to find the truth behind the city's destruction.
completionRequirements: About the Old School RuneScape Wiki

name: Desert Treasure I
description: Desert Treasure I is a quest surrounding the Mahjarrat Azzanadra's escape from his pyramid prison in the Kharidian Desert. The quest is known for rewarding players with the powerful Ancient Magicks spellbook.
completionRequirements: Desert Treasure II - The Fallen Empire
About the Old School RuneScape Wiki

name: Icthlarin's Little Helper
description: Icthlarin's Little Helper is the second quest in the Kharidian quest series. The quest introduces the Menaphite demigod Icthlarin and explores the city of Sophanem.
completionRequirements: About the Old School RuneScape Wiki

name: Tears of Guthix
description: Tears of Guthix is a quest where you must help Juna, a follower of Guthix, restore a cavern in the Lumbridge Swamp Caves. Within the dungeon the walls flow with tears, a relic of Guthix's horror at the destruction during the God Wars. Completion of the quest grants access to the eponymous minigame, where it rewards experience in the player's lowest skill each time it is played.
completionRequirements: About the Old School RuneScape Wiki

name: The Lost Tribe
description: The Lost Tribe is the first quest in the Dorgeshuun quest series. Sigmund, the advisor to the Duke of Lumbridge tasks you to investigate sightings of goblins emerging from a newly formed crack in the castle's basement. The goblins turn out to be the pacifist Dorgeshuun tribe which has been lost from history for many years.
completionRequirements: About the Old School RuneScape Wiki

name: The Giant Dwarf
description: The Giant Dwarf is the first quest in the Rise of the Red Axe quest series. It involves the dwarven capital Keldagrim and The Red Axe consortium who are in control of the city.
completionRequirements: 2.3 An axe fit for a king
Star Wars: Episode IV â A New Hope
About the Old School RuneScape Wiki

name: Recruitment Drive
description: Recruitment Drive is the first quest in the Temple Knight series. It marks the first appearance of Sir Tiffy Cashien, who recruits you for the Temple Knights. However, the recruitment process involves several puzzles to test your wits.
completionRequirements: About the Old School RuneScape Wiki

name: Mourning's End Part I
description: Mourning's End Part I is a quest in the elf quest series, continuing directly where Roving Elves left off. The player travels to Lletya, the hideout of the rebel elves, to assist their leader Arianwyn in bringing down the Iorwerth clan. The first half of this two-part quest revolves around infiltrating their base in West Ardougne.
completionRequirements: About the Old School RuneScape Wiki

name: Forgettable Tale...
description: Forgettable Tale of a Drunken Dwarf is the second quest in the Rise of the Red Axe quest series, in which you must track down clues to find the truth behind the Red Axe corporation. It is the sequel to The Giant Dwarf quest.
completionRequirements: About the Old School RuneScape Wiki

name: Garden of Tranquillity
description: Garden of Tranquillity is a quest that focuses on the garden of Queen Ellamaria of Varrock. The queen needs a farmer to tend to her garden as a surprise for her husband, King Roald.
completionRequirements: 3.1 Elstan, farming patch south of Falador
3.2 Lyra, farming patch west of Port Phasmatys
3.3 Kragen, farming patch north of Ardougne
3.6 Bernald, The Toad and Chicken in Burthorpe
4.1 Statue of a former king, Lumbridge
About the Old School RuneScape Wiki

name: A Tail of Two Cats
description: A Tail of Two Cats is an intermediate quest about the life of Bob the Cat. It is the first quest to feature Robert the Strong and introduces the Dragonkin.
completionRequirements: The Hitchiker's Guide to the Galaxy
About the Old School RuneScape Wiki

name: Wanted!
description: Wanted! is the second quest in the Temple Knight series. Due to an oversight during your recruitment to the Temple Knights, you must now hunt down an extremely dangerous wizard and mass murderer named Solus Dellagar.
completionRequirements: About the Old School RuneScape Wiki

name: Mourning's End Part II
description: Mourning's End Part II (The Temple of Light), is the seventh quest in the Elf quest series. This quest is often described as challenging by players who have completed it due to it having a very difficult quest puzzle while being under attack by medium-level monsters.
completionRequirements: About the Old School RuneScape Wiki

name: Rum Deal
description: Rum Deal is the first quest in the pirate quest series, centering around the task of getting the production of 'rum' restarted as a band of angry, protesting undead pirates stake out Braindeath Island.
completionRequirements: About the Old School RuneScape Wiki

name: Shadow of the Storm
description: Shadow of the Storm is a quest that continues the plot of Demon Slayer. It involves the villain Denath once more, as well as his group of followers attempting to summon a dangerous demon named Agrith-Naar.
completionRequirements: About the Old School RuneScape Wiki

name: Making History
description: Making History is a quest about the restoration of the outpost north of West Ardougne and preventing it from being destroyed. During the quest, major parts of Kandarin's history are revealed.
completionRequirements: About the Old School RuneScape Wiki

name: Ratcatchers
description: Ratcatchers is a quest in which you help various people with rat-related problems. The quest introduces the Rat Pits, a collection of underground arenas where cats train and fight.
completionRequirements: About the Old School RuneScape Wiki

name: Spirits of the Elid
description: Spirits of the Elid is a quest in which players must assist the villagers of Nardah in restoring water to their town, which has all but disappeared. The villagers believe themselves to be the victim of a curse, but the truth must be discovered of what happened to the village's water sources.
completionRequirements: About the Old School RuneScape Wiki

name: Devious Minds
description: Devious Minds is a quest involving a plot against the clergy of Entrana. The quest connects to the Temple Knight storyline and the Mahjarrat storyline.
completionRequirements: About the Old School RuneScape Wiki

name: The Hand in the Sand
description: The Hand in the Sand is an intermediate quest revolving around the mysterious discovery of a severed hand in Bert's sand pit in Yanille. The quest is notable for having lots of puns and jokes in its dialogue.
completionRequirements: About the Old School RuneScape Wiki

name: Enakhra's Lament
description: Enakhra's Lament is a quest which takes place in an old temple beneath the Kharidian Desert. It is the first quest to feature the Mahjarrat Akthanakos and Enakhra.
completionRequirements: 2.3 The Camel, the Witch and the Prison
Desert Treasure II - The Fallen Empire
About the Old School RuneScape Wiki

name: Cabin Fever
description: Cabin Fever is the second quest in the Pirate quest series. During the quest, you learn to become a pirate by aiding the shifty Bill Teach in running his ship. The quest ends with access to the pirate island of Mos Le'Harmless.
completionRequirements: About the Old School RuneScape Wiki

name: Fairytale I - Growing Pains
description: Fairytale I - Growing Pains is a quest following Lost City set in Zanaris, the fairies' world and Gielinor's moon. The quest is focused on the Fairy Queen's encounter with a dangerous tanglefoot and her replacement, the Fairy Godfather.
completionRequirements: About the Old School RuneScape Wiki

name: Recipe for Disaster
description: Recipe for Disaster is the 100th quest released by Jagex, being a sequel to the Cook's Assistant quest. It is composed of 10 parts: the introduction, followed by 8 subquests, then culminating in a grand finale where the player must face-off with the Culinaromancer. The subquests range in difficulty from very easy to very hard. It is intended to be a quest which nearly any member can start, but which only the most accomplished and willing players can complete. It is most known for rewarding the player with the ability to buy Barrows gloves.
completionRequirements: About the Old School RuneScape Wiki

name: In Aid of the Myreque
description: In Aid of the Myreque is the second quest in the Myreque quest series, and follows the events of In Search of the Myreque. After discovering the secret group called the Myreque, the player must now help them move to a new location in Burgh de Rott, where they would be closer to the heart of their vampyre oppressors.
completionRequirements: 2.2 Preparing to travel to Burgh de Rott
2.4 Clearing out the rubble from the bar basement
About the Old School RuneScape Wiki

name: A Soul's Bane
description: A Soul's Bane is a combat-focused quest focused on helping Launa Talvoy find her son, who disappeared into a mysterious rift 25 years ago.
completionRequirements: About the Old School RuneScape Wiki

name: Rag and Bone Man I
description: Rag and Bone Man I is a quest during which you collect bones for the Odd Old Man to help complete his strange collection.
completionRequirements: About the Old School RuneScape Wiki

name: Swan Song
description: Swan Song is a quest about the adventuring life of the Wise Old Man. His help is requested in aiding the Piscatoris Fishing Colony get rid of a sea troll invasion. He views this quest as his "swan song", that is, his final adventure before retiring.
completionRequirements: About the Old School RuneScape Wiki

name: Royal Trouble
description: Royal Trouble is a Fremennik quest that takes you to Miscellania. Mysterious robberies threaten to plunge the island into a war with neighbouring Etceteria and, as regent, you are to investigate the occurrences to prevent this from happening.
completionRequirements: Monty Python and the Holy Grail
About the Old School RuneScape Wiki

name: Death to the Dorgeshuun
description: Death to the Dorgeshuun is the second quest in the Dorgeshuun quest series and sees the return of Sigmund, who attempts to destroy the Dorgeshuun once again. It also sees the first appearance of Zanik, the series' main protagonist.
completionRequirements: 2.3 If the Tears of Guthix quest has already been completed
2.4 If Tears of Guthix has not been completed
About the Old School RuneScape Wiki

name: Fairytale II - Cure a Queen
description: Fairytale II - Cure a Queen is the third quest in the Fairy Tale quest series.
completionRequirements: All's Fairy in Love and War
About the Old School RuneScape Wiki

name: Lunar Diplomacy
description: Lunar Diplomacy is a quest focusing on the feud between the mainland Fremennik and the Moon Clan. Completion grants access to Lunar Isle, and a new spellbook.
completionRequirements: 2.3.1 1. A game of chance (green/yellow south-western platform)
2.3.3 3. Chop, Chop, Chop away! (blue north-eastern platform)
2.3.4 4. Where am I? (white north-western platform - pink on iOS)
2.3.5 5. The race is on! (yellow-green eastern platform)
2.3.6 6. Anything you can do... (teal south-eastern platform)

name: The Eyes of Glouphrie
description: The Eyes of Glouphrie is a quest revolving around yet another plot against the Grand Tree gnomes, this time not by Glough, but a much more feared figure from gnomish history.
completionRequirements: About the Old School RuneScape Wiki

name: Darkness of Hallowvale
description: Darkness of Hallowvale is the third quest in the Myreque series, and involves travelling to Meiyerditch to contact the Myreque faction hidden there.
completionRequirements: About the Old School RuneScape Wiki

name: The Slug Menace
description: The Slug Menace is the second quest in the Sea Slug quest series, and was the update to greatly expand upon the small fishing village of Witchaven.
completionRequirements: About the Old School RuneScape Wiki

name: Elemental Workshop II
description: The Elemental Workshop II is the second quest in the Elemental Workshop series. You discover more about the mysterious workshop as you solve puzzles to create a mind helmet and mind shield.
completionRequirements: About the Old School RuneScape Wiki

name: My Arm's Big Adventure
description: My Arm's Big Adventure is the fourth quest in the troll series. In the quest you must aid My Arm, a young troll who wishes to prove himself by growing his own goutweed. This necessitates gathering goutweed tubers, teaching My Arm how to farm, and fighting a Giant Roc which takes poorly to My Arm's farming attempt.
completionRequirements: About the Old School RuneScape Wiki

name: Enlightened Journey
description: Enlightened Journey is a quest in which you help the Entrana monk Auguste set up his novel Balloon transport system.
completionRequirements: About the Old School RuneScape Wiki

name: Eagles' Peak
description: Eagles' Peak is a quest based on the Hunter skill, where the player helps the Ardougne Zoo procure a ferret as a new attraction. Rewards for the quest includes a new way to train the Hunter skill and a new form of transportation.
completionRequirements: About the Old School RuneScape Wiki

name: Animal Magnetism
description: Animal Magnetism is a quest during which the player helps Ava in Draynor Manor. The quest is required to access Ava's devices, robust ranged cape slot items.
completionRequirements: a phrase of the same name
About the Old School RuneScape Wiki

name: Contact!
description: Contact! is the sequel to Icthlarin's Little Helper and the third installment in the desert quest series. It deals with the quarantine of Sophanem imposed by neighbouring Menaphos.
completionRequirements: 2.4 I Spy with my Little Eye
About the Old School RuneScape Wiki

name: Cold War
description: Cold War is currently the only quest in the penguin quest series. It involves two agents finding out about the plans of the penguins, and requires you to go undercover as a penguin spy on the iceberg in the Lunar Sea.
completionRequirements: Star Wars Episode IV: A New Hope
About the Old School RuneScape Wiki

name: The Fremennik Isles
description: The Fremennik Isles is a quest about the two Fremennik islands Jatizso and Neitiznot, who are under the threat of invading ice trolls but also have a feud with each other.
leadDevelopers: Chihiro Y, Ben W, Douglas H
completionRequirements: About the Old School RuneScape Wiki

name: The Great Brain Robbery
description: The Great Brain Robbery is the third quest in the pirate quest series. In the quest, you help a group of Saradominist monks from Harmony Island. Their once peaceful island has been taken over by a horde of zombie pirates, led by Mi-Gor, a very dangerous individual.
completionRequirements: Star Wars: Episode IV â A New Hope
About the Old School RuneScape Wiki

name: What Lies Below
description: What Lies Below is a quest that deals with the Dagon'hai, an order of powerful Zamorakian mages. During the quest you team up with the Varrock Palace Secret Guard to help capture Surok Magis.
completionRequirements: Pirates of the Caribbean: The Curse of the Black Pearl
About the Old School RuneScape Wiki

name: Olaf's Quest
description: Olaf's Quest is a quest about the unfortunate Fremennik Olaf Hradson, whose boat has crashed, rendering him unable to find his grandfather's treasure. You must help him find it and make sure his family does not find out about his failure.
completionRequirements: About the Old School RuneScape Wiki

name: Another Slice of H.A.M.
description: Another Slice of H.A.M. is the third quest in the Dorgeshuun quest series. It involves another plot orchestrated by Sigmund to destroy the Dorgeshuun, this time involving the dwarves.
completionRequirements: About the Old School RuneScape Wiki

name: Dream Mentor
description: Dream Mentor is a Fremennik Quest taking place on Lunar Isle. It revolves around helping an adventurer conquer his fear of combat using oneiromancy.
completionRequirements: About the Old School RuneScape Wiki

name: Grim Tales
description: Grim Tales is a master quest that revolves around collecting a couple of rare items for Sylas, a peculiar collector. It contains many references to various real-life fairy tales.
completionRequirements: About the Old School RuneScape Wiki

name: King's Ransom
description: King's Ransom is the final quest in the Camelot quest series, released on 24 July 2007. The player must foil a plot from the Sinclair family and Morgan le Faye to destroy Camelot and the Knights of the Round Table.
completionRequirements: Harry Potter and the Philosopher's Stone
About the Old School RuneScape Wiki

name: Shilo Village
description: Shilo Village is a quest in which the player lays to rest a vengeful spirit that is attacking Shilo Village, a town located in southern Karamja. The quest unlocks access to the village and its cart system.
completionRequirements: 2.3 Scrolls from Ah Za Rhoon and the proper burial
About the Old School RuneScape Wiki

name: Biohazard
description: Biohazard continues the storyline after the Plague City quest. The plot deepens as Elena finally gets a chance to process her plague samples. Buried under these samples lies a well-hidden secret.
completionRequirements: About the Old School RuneScape Wiki

name: Tower of Life
description: Tower of Life is a quest in which a group of alchemists attempt to create a living being. It features some difficult choices about the future of this creature.
completionRequirements: About the Old School RuneScape Wiki

name: Rag and Bone Man II
description: Rag and Bone Man II is the sequel to Rag and Bone Man I, and involves collecting a large number of assorted bones for the Odd Old Man's collection.
completionRequirements: About the Old School RuneScape Wiki

name: Land of the Goblins
description: Land of the Goblins is the fourth quest in the Dorgeshuun quest series, where you and Zanik, at Grubfoot's request, attempt to find Yu'biusk - the homeland of the goblin race. It is the first quest to be backported into Old School RuneScape.
completionRequirements: About the Old School RuneScape Wiki

name: While Guthix Sleeps
description: While Guthix Sleeps is a grandmaster quest that was backported from its original release in 2008. Changes were made upon its release to Old School RuneScape to maintain the integrity of modern quests and account for continuity deviations from the original Mahjarrat storyline.
completionRequirements: 6.2 Trading Orbs For Blocks, Blocks for Access
About the Old School RuneScape Wiki

name: Zogre Flesh Eaters
description: Zogre Flesh Eaters is a Feldip Hills area quest in which you must venture into the crypts of Gu'Tanoth, an ogre resting ground, now crawling with undead zombie and skeleton ogres.
completionRequirements: About the Old School RuneScape Wiki

name: Monkey Madness II
description: Monkey Madness II: The Renegade Returns is the sequel to Monkey Madness I, and was the first quest to be created after the release of Old School RuneScape. Following the events of Monkey Madness I, Glough has vanished, prompting King Narnode Shareen to enlist the player's help once more in tracking down the war criminal and uncovering his next evil plan.
leadDevelopers: Mod Jed, Ian Gower, Mod Ash, Mod Maz, Mod Bond, Mod Ian
completionRequirements: About the Old School RuneScape Wiki

name: Client of Kourend
description: Client of Kourend is the first quest which involves the kingdom of Great Kourend, and is the 131st quest on Old School RuneScape.
completionRequirements: About the Old School RuneScape Wiki

name: The Queen of Thieves
description: The Queen of Thieves is a quest that follows on from Client of Kourend in the Great Kourend quest series. It was announced on the 6th of July 2017 and polled as part of the Old School Content Poll #57.
completionRequirements: About the Old School RuneScape Wiki

name: Bone Voyage
description: Bone Voyage is a quest about the construction of a barge for the Varrock museum. The quest unlocks Fossil Island, which is of archaeological interest to the museum Curator Haig Halen.
completionRequirements: About the Old School RuneScape Wiki

name: Dragon Slayer II
description: Dragon Slayer II: The Legacy of Elvarg is a quest that was released on 4 January 2018. It was announced during RuneFest 2017, and is a sequel to the original Dragon Slayer I quest, which was released in 2001. Following the player's defeat of Elvarg, Crandor is now (fairly) safe to investigate; one such researcher, Dallas Jones, seeks to investigate Elvarg's lair in hopes of uncovering the mystery behind her attack on the island.
completionRequirements: About the Old School RuneScape Wiki

name: The Depths of Despair
description: The Depths of Despair is a quest that follows on from Client of Kourend in the Great Kourend quest series. It was announced on the 9th of October 2017 and polled as part of the Old School Content Poll #57.
completionRequirements: About the Old School RuneScape Wiki

completionRequirements: About the Old School RuneScape Wiki

name: Tale of the Righteous
description: Tale of the Righteous is a quest announced on 21 March 2018[1] and polled in Old School Content Poll #58, which it passed. It follows Client of Kourend in the Great Kourend quest series.
completionRequirements: About the Old School RuneScape Wiki

name: Making Friends with My Arm
description: Making Friends with My Arm is a master quest in the troll quest series that follows on from My Arm's Big Adventure. It was first announced during RuneFest 2016 on 17 September 2016 and polled on 15 August 2018 as part of the Raise your hands for My Arm? poll.
completionRequirements: About the Old School RuneScape Wiki

name: Recipe for Disaster/Defeating the Culinaromancer
completionRequirements: About the Old School RuneScape Wiki

name: Song of the Elves
description: Song of the Elves is the final quest in the Elf quest series. The quest was announced at RuneFest 2018 and was released on 25 July 2019. Completion of the quest unlocks access to the elven city of Prifddinas.
leadDevelopers: Development and testing: Mod Ed, Mod Curse, Mod Lenny, Mod TideArt and graphics: Mod Gee, Mod Ghost, Mod West, Mod RyAudio: Mod Ian, Mod Slippers, Mod Surma

name: The Ascent of Arceuus
description: The Ascent of Arceuus is a quest in the Great Kourend quest series which focuses on Arceuus.
completionRequirements: About the Old School RuneScape Wiki

name: The Forsaken Tower
description: The Forsaken Tower is a quest in the Great Kourend quest series which focuses on Lovakengj. The player is tasked to retrieve Dinh's hammer from the Forsaken Tower to repair the damage on the Doors of Dinh, used to imprison Wintertodt in its prison.
completionRequirements: About the Old School RuneScape Wiki

name: The Fremennik Exiles
description: The Fremennik Exiles is the fourth quest in the Fremennik quest series. Here, the player assists Brundt the Chieftain in a simple investigation and what they discover gets them exiled from Rellekka by the Fremennik Council of Elders. With the help of Brundt, the player must regain the trust of the Council and save the Fremennik Province from an ancient threat.
completionRequirements: Harry Potter and the Philosopher's Stone
About the Old School RuneScape Wiki

name: Defender of Varrock
description: Defender of Varrock is a quest in the Mahjarrat storyline. During the quest, an investigation results in the discovery of a looming invasion by the Mahjarrat Zemouregal, with an undead army led by the enslaved hero Arrav. The quest is a backport of the RuneScape quest of the same name; it is the third quest to be backported into Old School RuneScape.
completionRequirements: About the Old School RuneScape Wiki

name: Sins of the Father
description: Sins of the Father is the fifth quest in the Myreque quest series. First announced at RuneFest 2019, the quest is of Master difficulty and involves a plan, hatched by The Myreque and Vanescula Drakan, to assassinate Lord Drakan himself.
completionRequirements: About the Old School RuneScape Wiki

name: A Kingdom Divided
description: A Kingdom Divided is a continuation of the Great Kourend quest series. The quest revolves around the hidden corruption within the Kourend Council and the discovery of a much deeper conspiracy hundreds of years in the making. It was first announced at RuneFest 2019.
completionRequirements: About the Old School RuneScape Wiki

name: A Porcine of Interest
description: A Porcine of Interest is a quest designed to introduce players to the Slayer skill. It added a new Slayer master, Spria, to the game as well as a new monster, the Sourhog.
completionRequirements: About the Old School RuneScape Wiki

name: Getting Ahead
description: Getting Ahead is an intermediate quest, and is the first of the Twisted Tales, which are short, standalone quests taking place in Great Kourend and the Kebos Lowlands.
completionRequirements: About the Old School RuneScape Wiki

name: A Night at the Theatre
description: A Night at the Theatre is a stand-alone quest in which the player assists the Mysterious Stranger in obtaining information about Verzik Vitur and the Theatre of Blood, culminating in completing a run of the Theatre.
completionRequirements: About the Old School RuneScape Wiki

name: Beneath Cursed Sands
description: Beneath Cursed Sands is the fourth quest in the Desert quest series, and is intended to introduce players to the lore surrounding Tombs of Amascut, the third raid. The quest added the Ruins of Ullek and the Necropolis to the south-eastern Kharidian Desert.
completionRequirements: About the Old School RuneScape Wiki

name: Temple of the Eye
description: Temple of the Eye is a quest accompanying the Guardians of the Rift minigame. The player assists Wizard Persten in investigating the properties of an unusual eye amulet; this leads to the discovery of the eponymous temple.
completionRequirements: Desert Treasure II - The Fallen Empire
About the Old School RuneScape Wiki

name: The Path of Glouphrie
description: The Path of Glouphrie is the sequel to The Eyes of Glouphrie in the gnome quest series, and the second quest to be backported into Old School RuneScape. During the quest, the investigation of Glouphrie's plans continues with an attempt to access the hidden city of Arposandra.
leadDevelopers: Mods Chihiro and Tytn (original), Mod Ed (Old School)
completionRequirements: About the Old School RuneScape Wiki

name: Sleeping Giants
description: Sleeping Giants is a quest accompanying the Giants' Foundry minigame. The player assists Kovac the giant in investigating an ancient workshop beneath the Giants' Plateau seemingly built by giants, for giants.
completionRequirements: 2.1 What is this? A workshop for giants?
About the Old School RuneScape Wiki

name: The Garden of Death
description: The Garden of Death is an intermediate quest that is part of the Twisted Tales series. First teased in the April 2022 Game Jam as one of Mod Ed's personal projects, the quest is similar to the Elemental Workshop quest series in that it focuses on exploration and discovery, instead of dialogue and cutscenes.
completionRequirements: Desert Treasure II - The Fallen Empire
About the Old School RuneScape Wiki

name: Desert Treasure II - The Fallen Empire
description: Desert Treasure II - The Fallen Empire is a grandmaster quest in the Mahjarrat series, and a sequel to Desert Treasure I. Billed as the hardest and longest quest released in Old School RuneScape to date, the quest features some of the most intensive combat encounters in the game and rewards players with the ability to fight four high-level bosses which drop the Virtus robes and pieces of both the soulreaper axe and ancient rings.
completionRequirements: 6 Duke Sucellus of the Sixth Legion

name: Secrets of the North
description: Secrets of the North is a quest in the Mahjarrat series announced during the Winter Summit 2022.
completionRequirements: Desert Treasure II - The Fallen Empire
About the Old School RuneScape Wiki

name: Children of the Sun
description: Children of the Sun is the first quest in the Twilight Emissaries series, which introduces players to Varlamore, the Shining Kingdom of the far west. In the quest, a delegation from Varlamore arrives in Varrock for a historic treaty signing with the rulers of Misthalin, but the visit is disrupted by a nefarious plot that the player must uncover.

About the Old School RuneScape Wiki

name: Perilous Moons
description: Perilous Moons is a quest introducing the players to Cam Torum, a dwarven settlement in Varlamore, and rewards access to the Moons of Peril boss encounter.

name: The Ribbiting Tale of a Lily Pad Labour Dispute
description: The Ribbiting Tale of a Lily Pad Labour Dispute, known by its shortened title Ribbiting Tale, is a quest in Varlamore set in the Locus Oasis in which players solve a ribbiting dispute and gain access to a new hardwood Farming patch.

name: Twilight's Promise
description: Twilight's Promise is a short quest set in the Civitas illa Fortis in eastern Varlamore, designed to introduce players to the kingdom and its features.

name: At First Light
description: At First Light is a quest in Varlamore that introduces players to the Hunter Guild.
completionRequirements: About the Old School RuneScape Wiki

name: The Heart of Darkness
description: The Heart of Darkness is the third quest in the Twilight Emissaries series, in which the player digs deeper into the Twilight Emissaries and sect of Ranul to figure out who's behind the attempts on Servius' life.
completionRequirements: About the Old School RuneScape Wiki

name: Death on the Isle
description: Death on the Isle is a murder mystery quest set on the island of Aldarin.

name: Meat and Greet
description: Meat and Greet is an experienced quest where the player helps introduce the tasty kebab to the kingdom.
completionRequirements: About the Old School RuneScape Wiki

name: Ethically Acquired Antiquities
description: Ethically Acquired Antiquities is a quest in which the player investigates a mysterious theft from the Fortis Grand Museum.
completionRequirements: About the Old School RuneScape Wiki
